{
  "stem": "23774.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then they put up a law strictly for Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Jews cannot walk on the street after, let's say, after 8 o'clock in the evening in summer.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Jews have to wear yellow patches on the front and in the back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you have to put up a star-- a Star of David paint on your house that they will recognize which one is Jewish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "To go in the market to buy something, they gave you just certain hours-- from 8:00 in the morning till 10:00.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And if you didn't follow their rules and regulation-- and their laws, the death penalty-- you'd get the death penalty.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we still lived in our homes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That was in 1941.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1941, when winter came, it was a very, very cold winter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the Germans came to the Judenrat, and they asked that we should give away all our winter clothes, like our furs and gloves and wood, because they have to send it to the front for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we were left without warm clothes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was no wood to heat the houses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we used to take demolished old houses and get the wood and burn in-- in the stoves to make sure that we get a little bit of heat.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then they used to give us 200, 250 grams of bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So you've-- only a working person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So let's say if I was working, I got 250 grams.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we were three people, because my older brother was in the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it wasn't enough.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Labor.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strictly labor, At the beginning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, in 1942, everybody in the city said, if you work in the sugar factory-- we had a big sugar factory-- that the [INAUDIBLE] had a concession of all the sugar factories.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
